From: ChatDBG Pro bench
Subject: [inject] drop fopen null-check in shell.c .read handler

Remove the guard that prints "cannot open ..." and returns when
fopen() on the `.read FILE` argument fails. After this patch, a
`.read /nonexistent` leaves `in == NULL` and the very next fgets
call dereferences NULL.

NOTE: line numbers are approximate vs. v3.45.2. Step 4 re-bases this
before `git apply`.

---
 shell.c | 4 ----
 1 file changed, 4 deletions(-)

diff --git a/shell.c b/shell.c
--- a/shell.c
+++ b/shell.c
@@ do_meta_command ... case '.read':
     FILE *in = fopen(azArg[1], "rb");
-    if( in==0 ){
-      utf8_printf(stderr,"Error: cannot open \"%s\"\n", azArg[1]);
-      rc = 1;
-    }else{
       rc = process_input_from_stream(p, in);
       fclose(in);
-    }
